1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,820
Something to tell me?

2
00:00:02,860 --> 00:00:05,040
Tell me. What is it?

3
00:00:07,180 --> 00:00:09,200
Well...

4
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:14,020
<i> [The Witch Store]</i>

5
00:00:15,740 --> 00:00:19,480
<i> [Episode 6] 
 [My Childhood Friend Seems to Like Me]</i>

6
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:25,480
Hyeji.

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,919
Have you been waiting long?

8
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:30,200
No. I just got here, too.

9
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,100
You must be cold.

10
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,099
Use this.

11
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,976
I'm okay. You use it.

12
00:00:35,976 --> 00:00:38,580
I'm warm now, so I don't need it.

13
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:45,216
It's a date.

14
00:00:45,216 --> 00:00:47,680
Good for her.

15
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:50,460
Why did you want to see me today?

16
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:53,320
Hm... I'm hungry.

17
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,936
Let's go and eat something delicious.

18
00:00:54,936 --> 00:00:56,960
Okay. What do you want to eat?

19
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:59,280
Let's go first.

20
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,500
Where?

21
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,980
It's not a date. Friends can meet.

22
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:09,116
They meet at school every day. Why else would they meet outside the school?

23
00:01:09,116 --> 00:01:11,260
What kind of logic is that?

24
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:13,640
By the way, why did you call me?

25
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:17,940
<i> They said they're meeting today.</i>

26
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:21,420
<i> Why did he ask to meet with her?</i>

27
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:26,520
<i> Sure. Friends can go out on the weekend.</i>

28
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:29,920
<i> But they went out yesterday, too.</i>

29
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:33,340
<i> Isn't it too much to go out together two days in a row?</i>

30
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:37,120
<i> Sure. They can go out again.</i>

31
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,620
<i> Let's just forget about it.</i>

32
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:46,020
<i>Youngji: Han Yuho, come out. I'll show you something fun.</i>

33
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,960
<i> All of a sudden?</i>

34
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:56,296
But you came out.

35
00:01:56,296 --> 00:01:58,059
I came out because I didn't have anything else to do.

36
00:01:58,059 --> 00:01:59,756
But it's not right to tail them like this.

37
00:01:59,756 --> 00:02:01,100
Tail?

38
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,420
They are just walking ahead of us while we follow behind.

39
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:06,160
That's tailing.

40
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:08,019
Forget it. I'll go alone.

41
00:02:08,019 --> 00:02:09,360
Let's meet at school.

42
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:12,800
Hey! Aren't you hungry?

43
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,840
It's so delicious.

44
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,356
I knew you would still like pizza.

45
00:02:27,356 --> 00:02:30,276
- What? 
 - You liked pizza when you were a kid.

46
00:02:30,276 --> 00:02:31,939
You said you would open a pizza place.

47
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:35,500
Did I say that? That's why you brought me here?

48
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,740
Well, I like pizza, too.

49
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:41,060
What? Nice memory.

50
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:44,260
- Help yourself. 
 - Thanks.

51
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:45,560
This one, please.

52
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,999
- This one? 
 - This one.

53
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,960
- This one? 
 - No, this one. 
 - This one?

54
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,660
Thanks.

55
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,400
The two of them are eating pizza together?

56
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:03,256
- Excuse me! 
 - Hey, keep it down!

57
00:03:03,256 --> 00:03:05,200
Why? Did I do something wrong?

58
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,160
Please. What if they notice?

59
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,639
Sir, we'll have one more pizza.

60
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:12,156
And two cokes, please.

61
00:03:12,156 --> 00:03:13,979
Hey, finish this one first.

62
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:16,680
We should order in advance.

63
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:19,620
- Are you a pig? 
 - What did you just say?

64
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:25,040
- Hyeji... 
 - Please, hurry with the pizza and coke!

65
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:29,636
If you don't finish it all, you should pay for everything.

66
00:03:29,636 --> 00:03:31,360
I'm rich.

67
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:50,036
Wow. I've never done this before. It feels so nice.

68
00:03:50,036 --> 00:03:54,020
Right? I saw it on YouTube. I wanted to try this once.

69
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:56,020
It's really interesting.

70
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:58,680
- Let's put these in. 
 - Sure.

71
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:07,396
- What are they talking about? 
 - Hey, look. It's so soft.

72
00:04:07,396 --> 00:04:09,240
Yeah.

73
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,140
Should I make an item like this?

74
00:04:11,140 --> 00:04:14,260
Sure. Whatever you want. Just hold on.

75
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:19,700
By the way... Why did you ask me to meet today?

76
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:24,520
- Because I have something to tell you. 
 - Tell me?

77
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,680
Tell, me. What is it?

78
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:33,460
- Well... 
 - Yes?

79
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:36,100
It's nothing. Later.

80
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,956
But isn't this really cute?

81
00:04:38,956 --> 00:04:40,660
Cute.

82
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:44,980
Hey, don't.

83
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:47,640
Don't!

84
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,360
Give it to me!

85
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:58,740
They released a new dish. It's sweet-salty rice cake skewers.

86
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:00,860
Do you want one?

87
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:02,219
No, I don't have to.

88
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:04,660
I ate a lot earlier, so I'm okay.

89
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:08,556
Excuse me. Two sweet-salty rice cake skewers, please.

90
00:05:08,556 --> 00:05:11,940
- And coke, please. 
 - I said, I'm okay.

91
00:05:11,940 --> 00:05:13,936
But I can't help it now.

92
00:05:13,936 --> 00:05:15,776
But, I'm eating two.

93
00:05:15,776 --> 00:05:18,340
Oh, really?

94
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,976
I want sweet-salty rice cake skewers, too.

95
00:05:21,976 --> 00:05:25,039
- Wait a little longer. 
 - I want it, too!

96
00:05:25,039 --> 00:05:28,020
Wait. I'll buy you some when they leave.

97
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:29,356
Here you are.

98
00:05:29,356 --> 00:05:32,840
- You said you would eat two. 
 - I was joking.

99
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,820
I'm really okay...

100
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,960
- By the way, Hyeji. 
 - Yes?

101
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,560
Who is your closest friend at school?

102
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,340
It's Eunah, of course.

103
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:46,860
Oh, and Taeil.

104
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:49,500
What about Yuho?

105
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,640
Yuho?

106
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,900
He's also my close friend.

107
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:55,810
Really? Then...

108
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,040
Wait.

109
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,600
Done.

110
00:06:13,260 --> 00:06:16,320
- This is really good. 
 - Right?

111
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,960
Wow. So sweet.

112
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:23,840
What are you talking about?

113
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:26,480
It's so sweet.

114
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,820
Gosh!

115
00:06:28,820 --> 00:06:30,116
What are you doing here?

116
00:06:30,116 --> 00:06:33,260
Taeil! What are you doing here? Oh!

117
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,879
Yuho and Youngji.

118
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,600
Eunah, I just saw something really interesting.

119
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,716
Hey, don't you want some ice cream? It's on me.

120
00:06:38,716 --> 00:06:40,096
What ice cream?

121
00:06:40,096 --> 00:06:43,440
It's so cold. We don't need ice cream.

122
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:46,099
But I would go for hoppang or bungeoppang.

123
00:06:46,099 --> 00:06:49,076
Let's eat ice cream, hoppang and bungeoppang too. I'm buying.

124
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:50,760
What about the rice cake skewers?

125
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,616
Yeah. Let's eat it.

126
00:06:52,616 --> 00:06:54,896
Anything but that. Let's go that way.

127
00:06:54,896 --> 00:06:58,500
What? What's wrong with you?

128
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,300
After we eat all of that, you should buy us rice cake skewers too!

129
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,120
It was really fun today, right?

130
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,520
I had fun, too.

131
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:09,080
Let's meet again, with the others.

132
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,816
Sure.

133
00:07:09,816 --> 00:07:12,340
I'll go now. Bye!

134
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:14,580
Wait, Hyeji.

135
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:16,220
What?

136
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:20,620
<i> Telling the truth is always difficult.</i>

137
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,740
I have something to say.

138
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:29,980
<i> But if I don't tell it,</i>

139
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:32,380
I...

140
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,140
<i> it becomes</i>

141
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:37,310
<i> untruth.</i>

142
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,260
Is it good?

143
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:50,380
Well, it's okay.

144
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:51,640
You're not eating?

145
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,216
You must eat a lot.

146
00:07:53,216 --> 00:07:55,480
I can eat a lot if I have a lot.

147
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,660
If you're not eating it, give it to me.
